  <section>
    <h2>Basic Inline Text</h2>
    <p>
      This is normal text with <b>bold (b)</b>, <strong>strong</strong>,
      <i>italic (i)</i>, <em>emphasis (em)</em>, <u>underline</u>,
      <mark>highlight</mark>, <small>small</small>, <del>deleted</del>,
      <ins>inserted</ins>, H<sub>2</sub>O, and E = mc<sup>2</sup>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Inline code: <code>&lt;span&gt;Hello&lt;/span&gt;</code>,
      variable: <var>x</var>, sample output: <samp>42</samp>,
      keyboard: <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>C</kbd>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Quotations & Semantics</h2>
    <p>
      Short inline quote: <q cite="https://example.com">Stay curious.</q>
      Cited work: <cite>Example Journal</cite>.
    </p>
    <blockquote cite="https://example.com">
      Blockquote: “Design is the silent ambassador of your brand.”
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      Abbreviation: <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr>,
      definition: <dfn>Accessibility</dfn> means inclusive design.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Preformatted & Code Block</h2>
